data.title: About: 3000 class railcar
data.meta_description: The 3000/3100 class are a class of diesel railcars operated by the State Transport Authority and its successors in Adelaide. They were built by Comeng and Clyde Engineering between 1987 and 1996 and are the workhorse of the non-electrified suburban rail network in Adelaide.
data.text:
dbo:abstract

The 3000/3100 class are a class of diesel railcars operated by the State Transport Authority and its successors in Adelaide. They were built by Comeng and Clyde Engineering between 1987 and 1996 and are the workhorse of the non-electrified suburban rail network in Adelaide. (en)

阿德萊德都會交通3000/3100形（英語：3000/3100 class），是於其鐵路網絡下使用的柴電鐵路車輛，由採購，並由及於1989至1996年間製造。 (zh)
